        <svcsubproc>
            <title>A. UTDS -- VISUAL (STATIC) TIMING CHECK</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assure the shut-off is in the no-fuel position before proceeding.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the key from the ignition.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Manually bar the engine in the normal direction of rotation until the timing pointer and
                    the specified degree mark on the crankshaft pulley are aligned.
                    <emph type="bold">Refer to Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500523">5.23</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    and the "PERFORMANCE DATA GUIDELINES" in this section for the static timing specification.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4500523" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg9301" filename="../figcg9/CG9301.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.23 Engine Timing Marks and Pointer Location</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Pulley with Timing Marks</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Timing Pointer</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove pipe plug located behind access cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Visually inspect timing mark (2,
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500524">5.24</hotlnk>)
                    </emph>
                    and timing pointer (1) to insure alignment.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If marks do not align, follow the "INJECTION PUMP FLOW TIMING" procedures outlined in
                    Fuel Injection Pump Service Manual CGES-200-2.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall pipe plug.</para>
                <figure id="ef4500524" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg6184" filename="../figcg6/CG6184.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.24 Injection Pump Timing Marks</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Timing Pointer</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Timing Mark on Pump Drive Shaft Hub</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>FLOW TIME ONLY WHEN:</para>
                        <seqlist style="arabic">
                            <item>
                                <para>PUMP TIMING POINTER IS MISSING.</para>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <para>PUMP TIMING POINTER IS BENT.</para>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <para>SCRIBE MARK ACCURACY IS QUESTIONABLE</para>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <para>SCRIBE MARK IS OBSCURED (NOT CLEARLY VISIBLE).</para>
                            </item>
                        </seqlist>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
                <para>Refer to UTDS Model 100 Fuel Injection Pump Service Manual CGES-200-2, Section 5 for Flow Timing
                    (Adjusting Port Closing) procedure.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>THIS PROCEDURE SHOULD NOT BE DONE ON ENGINE. FLOW TIMING MUST TAKE PLACE IN A WELL
                            EQUIPPED SHOP UNDER CLEAN CONDITIONS.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
